data.value:
Please note: This tool ships with pre-generated SQL meta data (RTM) as showned in right list. If this machine ever installed other SQL server products, or you have applied any service pack/CU to SQL server , you need to specify media folder for the tool to get the latest SQL product meta data information(like product code, version, upgrade code etc) , otherwise the report could be incomplete. For example, if SQL2016 CU6 is ever installed you need to extract CU6 to a folder and specify this folder in above. The media folder can look like below:
C:\SQLSetup\RTMCU1 C:\SQLSetup\RTMCU6 C:\SQLSetup\SP1 C:\SQLSetup\SP1CU3
Then you can input the root folder, C:\SQLSetup, for the tool to scan.
For next run of the tool you can choose "Use cached meta data" option to save scan time. Please see Help->Manual for more information.
